Student 1: What is your assessment of the assignment? Was it helpful?
Was it fun?

I think the assignment was quite tedious and not being able to see
the full source code made debugging quite hard to approach at first.
I did not know how to use gdb efficiently, so I spent a lot of time
on the first part. Thinking through the invariants for part 2 was
quite helpful for understanding the code and for debugging in general.
However, I think reading the code was quite difficult for me. I thought
the assignment will be quite helpful for future classes through, 
especiallly as I work to debug more. 

