What warnings does critTer generate on checkerDT.c, and what are your
disagreements with them? Copy the critTer warnings here, and express
your disagreement after each warning. If there are no warnings, then
write "None."

   checkerDT.c: line 23: low priority: 
   A loop should consist of fewer than 35 lines;
   this loop consists of 52 lines; consider refactoring

   I disagree with this warning because for this loop, I am
   checking a lot of conditions relating to the node's children,
   which is why the loop consists of so many lines. Not only am
   I checking that the children and its path are not null, the
   child's parent is the node oNNode itself, and that the node
   and child are not the same. I am also checking whether there
   are duplicate children and that they are in lexicographic order.

   I could have shortened the for loop and instead just used 2 
   for loops, but because I use the index variable in multiple
   parts of the code, I decided to make the loop remain a bit
   longer. 

